{"document_id": "7568f8e67bea4c959a480fd295d29db7__0", "text": "ER triage — Lilavati Hospital Encounter ENC-2024-0915-001\nAnita Patil 32 Female Ward ER Bed 03\nArrived by ambulance vehicle MH01AB1234\nRelative Vikram Patil Phone 9876543210 Dr Dr. Sameer Deshmukh\nVitals / acuity: Patient conscious, oriented, vitals stable. Complaining of severe headache and dizziness for the past 2 hours. No fever. Blood pressure 140/90 mmHg. Pulse 98 bpm. Respiratory rate 18/min. SpO2 98% on room air.\n\nNursing Notes:\nPatient is a 32-year-old female oil expeller from Mumbai Suburban, Maharashtra, currently married, with middle education. She speaks English and Marathi. She reports a sudden onset of throbbing headache, described as 8/10 in intensity, associated with nausea but no vomiting. Denies any visual changes, neck stiffness, or weakness in limbs. No history of similar episodes. Patient appears anxious and is repeatedly checking her pulse. She has a known history of hypertension, diagnosed 6 months ago. She reports compliance with her medications, which she keeps in her purse. No known allergies. Last meal was 4 hours ago. No recent travel or sick contacts. Patient is alert and oriented x3. Neurological examination reveals no focal deficits. Fundoscopy shows mild papilledema. IV access established in left forearm with 18G cannula. Blood sample sent for CBC, electrolytes, and random blood sugar. Patient advised to lie down and rest. Pain score reduced to 5/10 after administration of paracetamol 500mg orally. Dr. Deshmukh has been informed and is evaluating the patient.", "tokenized_text": ["ER", "triage", "—", "Lilavati", "Hospital", "Encounter", "ENC", "-", "2024", "-", "0915", "-", "001", "Anita", "Patil", "32", "Female", "Ward", "ER", "Bed", "03", "Arrived", "by", "ambulance", "vehicle", "MH", "01", "AB", "1234", "Relative", "Vikram", "Patil", "Phone", "9876543210", "Dr", "Dr", ".", "Sameer", "Deshmukh", "Vitals", "/", "acuity", ":", "Patient", "conscious", ",", "oriented